Debra LaFave, a former schoolteacher, faces accusations of having a sexual relationship with a 14-year-old student.
She plans to plead insanity to avoid trial.
Prosecutors released evidence supporting their claims, including photographs and recorded tapes.
The victim's family wants closure, while LaFave's ex-husband cites mental health issues.
Despite plea negotiations breaking down, a plea deal was eventually reached.
LaFave will lose her teaching certificate, register as a sexual predator, and face restrictions.
Media attention and legal complexities have made this case highly publicized and controversial, raising questions about justice and media influence.
